CARRELL v. UNITED STATES. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. January 22, 1918. Rehearing Denied March 11, 1918.) No. 3089. In Error to the District Court of the United States for the Northern District of Texas; Edward R. Meek, Judge. W. J. Carrell was convicted of crime, and he brings error. Affirmed. Wm. H. Atwell, of Dallas, Tex., and D. W. Odell, of Ft. Worth, Tex., for plaintiff in error. Wilmot M. Odell, U. S. Atty., of Ft. Worth, Tex., and Wm. E. Allen, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Dallas, Tex.

Before WALKER and BATTS, Circuit Judges, and GRUBB, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

There was no reversible error in any ruling presented for review in this case. The questions raised are not such as to call for comment or discussion. The judgment is affirmed.
